{"created":"2014-11-25T17:07:53+00:00","modified":"2015-05-14T21:11:47+00:00","valid":{"from":"2015-05-14T21:11:47+00:00","to":"3015-05-14T21:11:47+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","title":"Guest DJ: Yusuf/Cat Stevens","published":"2014-11-25T19:11:00+00:00","teaser":"Yusuf/Cat Stevens joins All Songs Considered hosts Bob Boilen and Robin Hilton to share songs that shaped his career and discuss his new album, <em>Tell 'Em I'm Gone. </em>","itags":["npr_api","366376203"],"guid":"41130d02-d486-46c8-91b7-295b473d91b9","contentencoded":"<p>Decades ago, the potent folk songs of Cat Stevens inspired <em>All Songs Considered </em>host Bob Boilen to pick up acoustic guitar. Now known as <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/artists/18378395/yusuf-islam\">Yusuf/Cat Stevens</a>, the singer visits the <em>All Songs </em>studio for this week's show to discuss his path to music and share songs that inspired him along the way. Yusuf/Cat Stevens' most recent album, <em><a href=\"http://www.npr.org/2014/10/19/356126366/first-listen-yusuf-tell-em-im-gone\">Tell 'Em I'm Gone</a></em>, features reworkings of a number of classic blues songs and originals. The record also includes collaborations with super-producer <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/artists/15302155/rick-rubin\">Rick Rubin</a> and harmonica player <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/artists/15771847/charlie-musselwhite\" target=\"_blank\">Charlie Musselwhite</a>. <em>Tell Em I'm Gone</em> is his first album since 2009's <em>Roadslinger</em>.  <div class=\"fullattribution\">Copyright 2015 NPR. To see more, visit <a href=\"http://www.npr.org/\">http://www.npr.org/</a>.<img src=\"http://www.google-analytics.com/__utm.gif?utmac=UA-5828686-4&utmdt=Guest+DJ%3A+Yusuf%2FCat+Stevens&utme=8(APIKey)9(MDAyOTcwNDAwMDEyODgyMDkwMTgwNzY3YQ001)\"/></div></p>","byline":"Robin Hilton","audio":[{"meta":{"duration":"2700"},"type":"audio/m3u","href":"http://api.npr.org/m3u/1366566031-e7bfaf.m3u?orgId=1&topicId=1039&aggIds=130267676&d=2700&story=366376203&ft=nprml&f=366376203"},{"href":"http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/11/25/a_clockwork_orange_soundtrack_duran_duran_sq-ab7ea3ab94ac76371e0095f98fbdb9f363665e19.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"crop":"square","height":"500","width":"500"}},{"href":"http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/11/25/tea_for_the_tillerman_sq-44e56484a0a42e48f1fb11ca0a3c9f7c8a22aa12.jpeg","type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"crop":"square","height":"300","width":"300"}},{"href":"http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/11/25/thebandcahoots_sq-1f0b40bf0879b9d3bca6aa3cab532364824fb2dc.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"crop":"square","height":"1297","width":"1297"}},{"href":"http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/11/25/curtismayfield_sq-13763cdb009523a38fb854a0e45eef8c5a6d96b0.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"crop":"square","height":"219","width":"219"}},{"href":"http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2014/11/25/yusuf-ed36c0d1ada1e37e8ca812d13df7502a25137005.jpg","type":"image/jpeg","meta":{"crop":"standard","height":"1462","width":"1949"}}]}